rComments: I had him a couple years ago and have never gotten over my disgust for him as a teacher. He presents radical Marxist economic and social analysis and historiography as non-controversial/indisputable *fact*. Irresponsible and reprehensible as both a scholar and pedagogue. An attempt at true "re-education" in the most totalitarian sense.

Overall Todd was a good prof.  His lectures were always quite provocative, and he speaks from a clear left-wing bias.  We explored an array of Canadian issues in this class, and he held interesting viewpoints on many of these. This was a pleasant class, and a great introduction to Canadian Studies!
